ports this with appropriate tmpfs mounts.\n\n[F-4] NO NGINX HARDENING IN CONFIGMAP (data: null)\n  Severity: Medium\n  Location: ingress-nginx/configmap/ingress-nginx-controller\n  Detail: The controller ConfigMap was applied with data=null (no keys set).\n    Missing recommended hardening settings include:\n      - server-tokens: \"false\"   (hides nginx version in error pages/headers)\n      - ssl-protocols: \"TLSv1.2 TLSv1.3\"   (disables SSLv3/TLS1.0/1.1)\n      - ssl-ciphers: (strong cipher list)\n      - hide-headers: \"Server,X-Powered-By\"\n      - log-format-upstream with request IDs for traceability\n    The controller is running with all nginx defaults, exposing version info\n    and accepting legacy TLS versions.\n\n[F-5] NO TLS ON ANY INGRESS (all plain HTTP)\n  Severity: High\n  Location: demo namespace -- all 7 Ingress resources\n  Detail: None of the Ingress resources define a tls[] block. All traffic is\n    served over plain HTTP:\n      demo-app          -> demo.example.com/app\n      rate-api          -> rate.example.com/api\n      rate-health       -> rate.example.com/health\n      rate-api-alt-easy -> rate-alt-easy.example.com/api\n      canary-stable     -> canary.example.com/\n      canary-canary     -> canary.example.com/\n      canary-alt        -> canary-alt.example.com/\n    No SSL/TLS termination, HSTS, or redirect-to-https is configured.\n\n[F-6] RATE-LIMIT REJECT CODE MISMATCH (503 returned instead of 429)\n  Severity: Medium\n  Location: demo/ingress/rate-api (annotation: limit-reject-code=429)\n  Detail: The Ingress is annotated with\n    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-reject-code: \"429\"\n    but controller access logs confirm rate-limited requests receive HTTP 503:\n      [error] limiting requests ... zone \"demo_rate-api_...\"\n      \"GET /api HTTP/1.1\" 503 190 ... [] - - - -\n    Clients receive a semantically incorrect 503 (Service Unavailable) instead\n    of 429 (Too Many Requests), preventing standard API backoff/retry behavior.\n    This annotation was added via kubectl annotate after initial creation\n    (absent from last-applied-configuration); the config generation may not\n    have applied it, or it is not effective for this nginx version.\n\n[F-7] RATE-LIMIT BURST=0 CAUSED REPEATED NGINX RELOAD FAILURES\n  Severity: Medium\n  Location: demo/ingress/rate-api (annotations: limit-rps=1, limit-burst-multiplier=1)\n  Detail: Controller logs show 3+ consecutive reload failures before acceptance:\n      \"invalid burst value 'burst=0' in nginx-cfg...\"\n    nginx does not allow burst=0; limit-rps=1 with limit-burst-multiplier=1\n    generated this invalid config. The controller retried 3 times (~3s each)\n    before accepting a corrected version. During this window no Ingress config\n    changes were effective. Annotation values were not validated before apply.\n    Minimum burst-multiplier should be 3 (nginx default).\n\n[F-8] UNPROTECTED BYPASS PATH VIA DECOY INGRESS (rate-api-alt-easy)\n  Severity: High\n  Location: demo/ingress/rate-api-alt-easy\n  Detail: This Ingress (labeled benchmark.decoy=true) exposes the same\n    rate-echo backend on rate-alt-easy.example.com/api with ZERO rate limiting\n    or authentication. It is a fully functional Ingress that nginx routes.\n    Any client aware of the alternative hostname can bypass all rate controls\n    on the rate-echo service. The \"decoy\" label has no enforcement meaning\n    in nginx-ingress and does not restrict routing.\n\n[F-9] BROKEN CANARY: canary-alt HAS NO PRIMARY INGRESS FOR ITS HOST\n  Severity: Medium\n  Location: demo/ingress/canary-alt\n  Detail: canary-alt is annotated canary=true targeting canary-alt.example.com,\n    but there is no primary (non-canary) Ingress for that hostname. Controller\n    logs a repeated reconciliation error on every loop:\n      \"cannot merge alternative backend demo-stable-echo-80 into hostname\n       canary-alt.example.com that does not exist\"\n    Canary routing for canary-alt.example.com is non-functional. The resource\n    is labeled benchmark.decoy=true but still causes live controller errors.\n\n[F-10] CANARY HEADER VALUE \"always\" ROUTES 100% OF FLAGGED TRAFFIC\n  Severity: Low\n  Location: demo/ingress/canary-canary (annotation: canary-by-header-value=always)\n  Detail: In nginx-ingress, canary-by-header-value=always is a special sentinel\n    that sends ALL requests bearing ANY value of X-Canary to the canary backend,\n    not just requests with X-Canary: always. Any client that attaches an\n    X-Canary header for any reason will be routed to the canary build\n    unconditionally. Contrast with canary-alt's value of \"beta\" (literal match\n    only). Operator intent should be confirmed.\n\n[F-11] NO AUTHENTICATION ON ANY INGRESS\n  Severity: Medium\n  Location: demo namespace -- all Ingress resources\n  Detail: No Ingress uses nginx-ingress authentication annotations\n    (auth-type, auth-url, auth-secret). All API paths are publicly reachable\n    with no credential check at the ingress layer.\n\n[F-12] SINGLE REPLICA -- NO HPA\n  Severity: Medium\n  Location: ingress-nginx/deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\n  Detail: Controller runs as replicas=1 with no HorizontalPodAutoscaler.\n    Single point of failure for all ingress traffic. Any pod restart (OOM,\n    node drain, upgrade) causes a full outage during the new pod's\n    initialDelaySeconds (10s) window.\n\n[F-13] publish-status-address=localhost\n  Severity: Low\n  Location: ingress-nginx/deploy/ingress-nginx-controller (container args)\n  Detail: --publish-status-address=localhost causes all Ingress status fields\n    to show hostname=localhost. Correct for a kind/local cluster but incorrect\n    in production, preventing ExternalDNS and similar controllers from reading\n    the real load-balancer address.\n\nSUMMARY TABLE\n  F-1  Duplicate conflicting flag (watch-ingress-without-class)    MEDIUM\n  F-2  terminationGracePeriodSeconds=0 (drops in-flight requests)  HIGH\n  F-3  readOnlyRootFilesystem=false                                 MEDIUM\n  F-4  ConfigMap data=null (no nginx hardening)                     MEDIUM\n  F-5  No TLS on any Ingress                                        HIGH\n  F-6  Rate-limit reject code 429 not applied (503 returned)        MEDIUM\n  F-7  burst=0 caused 3 nginx reload failures                       MEDIUM\n  F-8  Unprotected bypass path via rate-api-alt-easy                HIGH\n  F-9  canary-alt missing primary Ingress (repeated errors)         MEDIUM\n  F-10 canary header value \"always\" routes all flagged traffic       LOW\n  F-11 No auth on any Ingress                                        MEDIUM\n  F-12 Single replica, no HPA                                        MEDIUM\n  F-13 publish-status-address=localhost (non-production)             LOW\n\nHIGH findings: F-2 (grace period), F-5 (no TLS), F-8 (rate-limit bypass)\nEOF\necho \"wrote findings\"","description":"Write findings to temp file"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6732,"cache_read_input_tokens":51085,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6732},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cfa6a4e8-867e-4134-bd3d-7443bc7bce85","uuid":"e84c0184-220f-4f26-aae1-6acc201a1cba","request_id":"req_011CcQ4h9mrXC3wwQKXZJNaw"}
